<br>
I have a theory on why we see diminishing returns on AC and why there seems to be a soft caps... The effectiveness of AC varies directly with the mobs atk and as we know EQ does not use smooth distributions, but discreet tables so that shifting from one to the next will result in a very large change in result for just a few points. Taking a wild guess (but now that we know the damage function, or part of it) lets say that every 10% difference of the mobs atk provides a shift on the table. When we are fighting mobs at the high end of the game, the steps betten damamge shifts become very large. <br>
<br>
For example, say fighting a mob with 1200 attack--having an AC around 1200 should produce that large step down we are used to seeing in mob damage (the radically shifted table where hits in the bottom 1/3 of the distribution become far more common) but the next step on the table is whopping 120 points of AC. <p><a href=http://www.topcities.com/VideoGames/kailyn/><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16294>Kailyn</a> <a href=http://www.topcities.com/VideoGames/kailyn/> Longstride</a> Warlord of the North, <a href=http://pub69.ezboard.com/bunleashedeq>Unleashed</a><br>
